<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="174" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,572,920]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,507,679,704]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[519,790,679,704]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="snethlageae">
<emphasis box="[519,790,679,704]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Loxopholis snethlageae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to western 
<taxonomicName box="[1073,1191,679,704]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="23" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazonia</taxonomicName>
, occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[1360,1431,679,704]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,264,716,741]" name="Colombia" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[321,373,717,740]" name="Peru" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[388,469,716,741]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1535,1557]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,277,1504]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,267,1513]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distribution of examined material of Loxopholis guianense, L. osvaldoi, L. snethlageae, and Micrablepharus atticolus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/581988/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
), distributed along the Solimões river system and the lower/median courses of its main tributaries (Negro, Purus, Tefé, Juruá, Jutaí, Ampiyacu, and Japurá Rivers). Until now it was only known from the type-locality and from the lower Purus River, in 
<collectingCountry box="[699,767,788,813]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Piagaçu-Purus Reserve—Waldez 
<emphasis box="[1163,1220,788,813]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">et al.</emphasis>
2013). In 
<collectingCountry box="[1337,1408,788,813]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it is only known from the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[508,630,824,848]" country="Peru" name="Amazonas" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[640,906,823,848]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="snethlageae">
<emphasis box="[640,906,823,848]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Loxopholis snethlageae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is terrestrial and diurnal, inhabits primary terra firme and disturbed (logged) forests, where it is found amid the leaf litter, root mass, bark litter and on the soil at base of trees (Ávila-Pires 1995; Waldez 
<emphasis box="[603,659,895,920]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">et al.</emphasis>
2013).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
